This is a study of animated gifs. I was curious about them.
Building it requires gmake-recipes also on github.

git clone git@github.com:kensmith/gmake-recipes.git

Edit GNUmakefile to point the variable gmake-recipes to the
filesystem path of your clone.

'make run' will build and run the program. The output file
glider.gif is an animated gif of a glider from the game of
life.

This code ignores LZW compression.

The included Lua program generated the glider data.

vim: tw=60:
